  "body": "# Built-in browser lacks privacy and potentially security\r\n\r\nI would love to see the feature enhancements for the built-in browser:\r\n\r\n### Setting for spoofing language\r\n\r\nOn android the system language or the keyboard **language settings get automatically transmitted to websites**. It would be nice if this could be optional spoofed if the user enabled this within the settings area as well as the timezone he is currently using. \r\n\r\n**Potential way to achieve this**\r\n\r\nUsage of en-us and UTC would be my proposal, \r\nsomething very similar like Firefox is using on private tabs on the desktop application.\r\n\r\n### Filter for Ad-/Malware\r\n\r\nMaybe as opt in as well or as opt out, your choice :)\r\n\r\nProtects users from many well known shady scripts, click hijacking, totally annoying adware.\r\nGoal would be a very nice usable browser without lacking functionality like broken websites etc. \r\nBrave like browsing experience, would mean blocking really dangerous sites and enhanced tracking protection.\r\n\r\n**Potential ways to achieve this**\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/gorhill/uBlock\r\nUsing the default filters \r\n\r\nSimply blocking well known trash spreader \r\nhttps://github.com/StevenBlack/hosts\r\nUnified hosts = (adware + malware) \r\n\r\nAlternatives for hosts filters:\r\nhttps://adaway.org/hosts.txt\r\nhttps://pgl.yoyo.org/adservers/serverlist.php?hostformat=hosts&showintro=0&mimetype=plaintext\r\n\r\n\r\nI don't like the idea of being to restrictive and block more than really necessary to protect the users of the application.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nGood PR since the project provides a solid and strong built-in browser feature and protects users privacy needs.\r\nFaster loading sites without annoying ad-/malware.\r\n\r\n**Summary** \r\n\r\nYou guys are awesome! I love the creation of multiple ETH accounts and the reproducible build on [F-Droid](https://f-droid.org/en/packages/im.status.ethereum/). Great job so far!\r\n",
